columns.name: Unique Key
columns.description: Unique identifier of a Service Request (SR) in the open data set. This is NOT the Service Request (SR) # provided to the initiating customer.  SR #s are not available in this data set.

columns.name: Created Date
columns.description: Date SR  was created

columns.name: Closed Date
columns.description: Date SR was closed by responding agency

columns.name: Agency
columns.description: Acronym of responding City Government Agency

columns.name: Agency Name
columns.description: Full Agency name of responding City Government Agency

columns.name: Complaint Type
columns.description: This is the fist level of a hierarchy identifying the topic of the incident or condition. Complaint Type may have a corresponding Descriptor (below) or may stand alone.

columns.name: Descriptor
columns.description: This is  associated to the Complaint Type, and provides further detail on the incident or condition. Descriptor values are dependent on the Complaint Type, and are not always required in SR.

columns.name: Location Type
columns.description: Describes the type of location used in the address information

columns.name: Incident Zip
columns.description: Incident location zip code, provided by geo validation.

columns.name: Incident Address
columns.description: House number of incident address provided by submitter.
